.bg-blue-500

with the hover:

.hover:bg-blue-500

Hover Classes


.hover:bg-*   ======= background color

.hover:text-{color}-{shade} == text color

.hover:font-bold ===== font weight

.hover:border-{color}-{shade} === border color


BUTTON EXAMPLE:

<body class="h-screen flex justify-center items-center">
<button class="bg-blue-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded">Submit</button>
</body>

Adding the hover with hover:bg-blue-600:

<button class="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-600 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded">Submit
</button>

TEST IT

Now changing the text color with hover:text-blue-500:

<button class="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-600 text-white hover:text-blue-500 font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded">
Submit
</button>




